cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.LG, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with modeling user search behavior and query auto-completion, which are core topics in IR.
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the inter-dependency among multiple events and their influence on user search behavior, which can be seen as a network of events influencing a network of users.
3. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper studies the influence of external factors on user search behavior, which is a topic of interest in social and behavioral sciences.
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a Joint Influence Model based on the Multivariate Hawkes Process, which is a machine learning technique.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses query-log data from https://search.yahoo.com/ and proposes a model to capture the temporal dynamics of joint influence, which involves data processing and algorithmic modeling.
